text:
At first I was slightly disappointed that Arinos is sort of a re-do of Flawless. Even though the context is quite different, we already had a magical fusion character. But thinking about it and rewatching, I realized most of the episode is just re-doing what happened in previous episodes but 'wrong.' I'm sure there are more but I was thinking about these:

Episode starts with phone call invitation to party (Pinkie Pie's Sleepover), but it's not the entire Mane 6.
Care Package seen with cartoonish hole in midsection like Big Mac (Soarin & Braeburn), but it's some weird fursuit.
Flashback to character's room with posters of character they like (Toola Roola & Star Song), but the relationship is only parasocial here.
Twilight spending time with Rarity and Sweetie Belle with Rarity's poverty as a focus (Unicorn Con), but Sweetie Belle is inexplicably deaged to what she was in that episode.
Random shot of character from film franchise (Sonic Rainboom), but whereas Frodo covers up a scene transition Qui Gon just appears randomly.
Rarity and serial killer theme (Leave Ponyville), but Rarity is the victim instead of the serial killer.
Villain dressed as nun (Death of Trixie), but obviously Care Package is not currently undergoing CBT.
Magical fusion character with confetti (Death of Twilight), but they seem inherently damaged and uncertain what they are. 
Discussion of Little Caesars (Twilight Shows Trixie), but they are eating pizza in bed which is gross. 

So when Soarin rewinds the last 5 days and goes "I've already heard this," yeah, I'm in the same boat dude. All the repetition/doubling in 'Coco Pommel' was there to foreshadow the masked pony being Trixie's twin, but I'm intrigued what all this is supposed to mean.
